<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>About | Rylu · AT 2013</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;1,400&family=Spectral:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;1,300;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --ink: #1a1410;
      --ink-muted: #6b5f54;
      --ink-faint: #a89d92;
      --paper: #f7f4ef;
      --paper-warm: #ede9e0;
      --accent: #4a3728;
      --border: rgba(74,55,40,0.12);
    }

    html { background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink); }
    body { font-family: 'Spectral', Georgia, serif; font-weight: 300; min-height: 100vh; }

    .top-nav {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 10;
      background: var(--paper);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 1.25rem 2rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      justify-content: space-between;
    }

    .nav-home {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .nav-home:hover { color: var(--ink-muted); }

    .content {
      max-width: 640px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 4rem 2rem 6rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
      font-weight: 400;
      font-style: italic;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      color: var(--ink);
    }

    p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: 1.5em;
    }

    .divider {
      width: 40px;
      height: 1px;
      background: var(--accent);
      opacity: 0.3;
      margin: 2.5rem 0;
    }

    h2 {
      font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .faq {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }

    .faq-item {}

    .faq-q {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink-faint);
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }

    .faq-a {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <nav class="top-nav">
    <a href="/" class="nav-home">Rylu · Appalachian Trail · 2013</a>
  </nav>

  <div class="content">
    <h1>About this journal</h1>

    <p>
      In the spring of 2013, I set out from Springer Mountain in Georgia and walked north along the Appalachian Trail toward Maine. This site is a record of that journey — 157 days, 2,186 miles.
    </p>

    <p>
      The entries were written day by day on an iPhone 4, usually at the end of a long day of hiking. Typing wasn't always what I wanted to be doing after ten or fifteen miles on foot, so some days are more detailed than others. The words are unpolished and unedited — written in the moment, left as they were.
    </p>

    <p>
      The photos were taken with a Sony DSC RX-100 and are completely (or almost completely) unedited. What you see is what the trail looked like.
    </p>

    <p>
      <i>- Doug Labbe (Rylu)</i>
    </p>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <h2>A few questions people ask</h2>

    <div class="faq">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Did you bring a gun?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">No. Way too heavy.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Did you go alone?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — but as you can see and read about, I was never really alone.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How did you get food?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Every two to five days the trail passes near or through a town. I'd walk or get a ride in, resupply at a grocery store or whatever was available, eat whatever I could in town, and head back out.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
